1a

gamblersRuin<-function(n1,n2,p){
  len<-0
  repeat {   
  a<-rbinom(1,1,p)
  if(a==1){
    n1<-n1+1
    n2<-n2-1
  } else{
    n1<-n1-1
    n2<-n2+1
  }
  len<-len+1
   if (n1==0||n2==0) {
    break
  } 
  }
  s<-c(len=len,n1=n1,n2=n2)
  return (s)
}
set.seed(2017)
gamblersRuin(n1 = 10, n2 = 10, p = 0.5)
## len  n1  n2 
## 196   0  20

2a

  1. Complete the function colSumsFor.
colSumsFor<- function(x){
v <- vector(length = ncol(x))
for (i in 1:ncol(x)) {
v[i]<-sum(x[,i])
}
names(v)<-colnames(x)
v
}
mat <- as.matrix(iris[, 1:4])
df <- iris[, 1:4]
colSumsFor(mat)
## Sepal.Length  Sepal.Width Petal.Length  Petal.Width 
##        876.5        458.6        563.7        179.9
#ii. Complete the function colSumsFor2.
colSumsFor2<-function(x) {
x <- as.matrix(x)
v <- vector(length = ncol(x))
for (i in 1:ncol(x)){
v[i]<-sum(x[ ,i])
}
names(v)<-colnames(x)
v
}
mat <- as.matrix(iris[, 1:4])
df <- iris[, 1:4]
colSumsFor2(mat)
## Sepal.Length  Sepal.Width Petal.Length  Petal.Width 
##        876.5        458.6        563.7        179.9
#iii. Complete the function colSumsApply.
colSumsApply <- function(x){ 
   apply(as.matrix(x), 2, sum)
}
colSumsApply(mat)
## Sepal.Length  Sepal.Width Petal.Length  Petal.Width 
##        876.5        458.6        563.7        179.9
#iv. Complete the function colSumsSapply.
colSumsSapply <- function(x) 
{ sapply(as.data.frame(x),sum)
}
colSumsSapply(mat)
## Sepal.Length  Sepal.Width Petal.Length  Petal.Width 
##        876.5        458.6        563.7        179.9
#v. Complete the function colSumsLapply.
colSumsLapply <- function(x) {
do.call(cbind, lapply(as.data.frame(x),sum))
}
colSumsLapply(mat)
##      Sepal.Length Sepal.Width Petal.Length Petal.Width
## [1,]        876.5       458.6        563.7       179.9
#vi. Issue the function colSumsCrossprod.
colSumsCrossprod <- function(x) { 
    crossprod(rep(1, nrow(x)), as.matrix(x))[1, ]
}
colSumsCrossprod(mat)
## Sepal.Length  Sepal.Width Petal.Length  Petal.Width 
##        876.5        458.6        563.7        179.9

df <- as.data.frame(matrix(rnorm(5000), 50, 100))
colSumsDf <- rbind(colSumsFor = system.time(replicate(n = 10000,colSumsFor(df))),colSumsFor2 = system.time(replicate(n = 10000, colSumsFor2(df))), colSumsApply = system.time(replicate(n = 10000, colSumsApply(df))), colSumsSapply = system.time(replicate(n = 10000, colSumsSapply(df))), colSumsLapply = system.time(replicate(n = 10000, colSumsLapply(df))), colSumsCrossprod = system.time(replicate(n = 10000, colSumsCrossprod(df))), colSums = system.time(replicate(n = 10000, colSums(df))))
